#. id="Bu-Pc.11">
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 11: the training rule on plants"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><p><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.11.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.226"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa338"></a>
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Āḷavī at the Aggāḷava Shrine."

msgstr "At that time the monks at Āḷavī were doing building work."

msgstr "And they cut trees and got them cut."

msgstr "Then, when a certain monk was cutting a tree, the deity that lived in it said to him, “Venerable, don’t cut down our dwelling because you want to build a dwelling for yourself.”"

msgstr "Not taking any heed, he just cut it down, and he hurt the arm of that deity’s child."

msgstr "That deity thought, “Perhaps I should just kill this monk?”"

msgstr "But then it reconsidered, “It wouldn’t be appropriate for me to just kill this monk."

msgstr "Why don’t I instead tell the Master about this matter?”"

msgstr "And it approached the Master and told him what had happened."

#. </p><p>
msgstr "“Well done, deity!"

msgstr "It’s good that you didn’t kill that monk."

msgstr "If you had killed that monk today, you would have made much demerit."

msgstr "The tree over there is empty;"

msgstr "take that as your dwelling.”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "People complained and criticized those monks, “How can the Sakyan ascetics cut trees and get them cut?"

msgstr "They are hurting life with one sense faculty.”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa339"></a>The monks heard the complaints of those people, and the monks of few desires …"

msgstr "complained and criticized those monks, <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.227"></a> “How can those monks at Āḷavī cut trees and get them cut?”…"

msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you do this?”"

msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them, “…"

msgstr "Foolish men, how can you cut trees and get them cut?"

msgstr "People regard trees as conscious."

msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p class="rule">
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa349"></a>‘If a monk destroys plants, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.11.2"></a>
msgstr "<a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.11.2.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa341"></a><strong class="term">Plants</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "there are five kinds of propagation:"

msgstr "propagation from roots, propagation from stems, propagation from joints, propagation from cuttings, propagation from seeds.</span>"

msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa342"></a><strong class="term">Propagation from roots</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "turmeric, ginger, sweet flag, white orris root, friar’s hood, hellebore, khus-khus, <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.228"></a> nut grass, or whatever other plants there are that are produced from roots, that grow from roots—"

msgstr "this is called “propagation from roots.”</span>"

msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa343"></a><strong class="term">Propagation from stems</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "the Bodhi tree, the banyan tree, the wave-leaved fig, the cluster fig, the <i lang="pi">kacchaka</i> fig-tree, the wood-apple tree, or whatever other plants there are that are produced from stems, that grow from stems—"

msgstr "this is called “propagation from stems.”</span>"

msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa344"></a><strong class="term">Propagation from joints</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "sugar-cane, bamboo, reed, or whatever other plants there are that are produced from joints, that grow from joints—this is called “propagation from joints.”</span>"

msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa345"></a><strong class="term">Propagation from cuttings</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "basil, rosha grass, <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.229"></a> fragrant swamp mallow, or whatever other plants there are that are produced from cuttings, that grow from cuttings—this is called “propagation from cuttings.”</span>"

msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa346"></a><strong class="term">Propagation from seeds</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "grains, vegetables, or whatever other plants there are that are produced from seeds, that grow from seeds—this is called “propagation from seeds.”</span>"

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p>
msgstr "<a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.11.2.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa347"></a>If it is capable of propagation, and he perceives that it is, and he cuts it or gets it cut, or he breaks it or gets it broken, or he cooks it or gets it cooked, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgstr "If it is capable of propagation, but he is unsure if it is, and he cuts it or gets it cut, or he breaks it or gets it broken, or he cooks it or gets it cooked, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If it is capable of propagation, but he perceives that it is not, and he cuts it or gets it cut, or he breaks it or gets it broken, or he cooks it or gets it cooked, there is no offense."

#. </p><p>
msgstr "If it is not capable of propagation, but he perceives that it is, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If it is not capable of propagation, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If it is not capable of propagation, and he perceives that it is not, there is no offense."

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p>
msgstr "<a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.11.2.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa348"></a>There is no offense:"

msgstr "if he says, “Consider this/give this/bring this/there’s need for this/make this allowable;”"

msgstr "if it is unintentional;"

msgstr "if he is not mindful;"

msgstr "if he does not know;"

msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta">
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa349"></a>The first rule, the training rule on plants, is finished."

#. </p><hgroup><h1>
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 12: the training rule on evasive speech"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><h3>
msgstr "First sub-story"

#. </h3><p>
msgstr "<a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.12.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.230"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa350"></a>At one time the Buddha was staying at Kosambī in Ghosita’s Monastery."

msgstr "At that time Venerable Channa was misbehaving."

msgstr "Then, when he was examined about an offense in the midst of the Order, he spoke evasively, “Who has committed an offense?"

msgstr "What offense has been committed?"

msgstr "In regard to what has an offense has been committed?"

msgstr "How has an offense been committed?"

msgstr "Who are you talking about?"

msgstr "What are you talking about?”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa351"></a>The monks of few desires …"

msgstr "complained and criticized him, “How can Venerable Channa speak evasively in this way when he is examined about an offense in the midst of the Order?’”…"

msgstr "“Is it true, Channa, that you are speaking like this?”"

msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

msgstr "The Buddha rebuked him, “…"

msgstr "Foolish man, when examined about an offense in the midst of the Order, how can you speak evasively, thus:"

msgstr "‘Who has committed an offense? What offense has been committed? In regard to what has an offense has been committed? How has an offense been committed? Who are you talking about? What are you talking about?’"

msgstr " This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …”…"

msgstr "and after criticizing him …"

msgstr "he gave a teaching and addressed the monks, “Well then, monks, let the Order charge Channa with evasive speech."

msgstr "And he is to be charged in this way."

msgstr "A competent and capable monk should inform the Order:"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.231"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa352"></a> ‘Venerables, let the Order listen to me."

msgstr "This monk Channa speaks evasively when examined about an offense in the midst of the Order."

msgstr "If it seems appropriate to the Order, the Order should charge him with evasive speech."

msgstr "This is the motion."

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa353"></a>Venerables, let the Order listen to me."

msgstr "This monk Channa speaks evasively when examined about an offense in the midst of the Order."

msgstr "The Order is charging him of evasive speech."

msgstr "Any monk who approves of charging him of evasive speech should remain silent."

msgstr "Any monk who does not approve should say so."

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa354"></a>The Order has charged the monk Channa of evasive speech."

msgstr "The Order approves and is therefore silent."

msgstr "I will remember it thus.’”"

#. </p></span><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa354"></a>After criticizing Channa in many ways for being difficult to support …"

msgstr "the Master said, “And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h3>
msgstr "Preliminary ruling"

#. </h3><p class="rule">
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa356"></a>‘If a monk speaks evasively, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa357"></a>In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. </p><h3>
msgstr "Second sub-story"

#. </h3><p>
msgstr "<a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.12.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa358"></a>Later, when Channa was again being examined about an offense in the midst of the Order, he thought, “By speaking evasively I’ll commit an offenses,” and he instead harassed the Order by remaining silent."

#. </p><p>
msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

msgstr "complained and criticized him, “When he’s examined about an offense in the midst of the Order, how can Venerable Channa harass the Order by remaining silent?’”…"

msgstr "“Is it true, Channa, that you are acting like this?”"

msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

msgstr "<a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.232"></a> The Buddha rebuked him, “…"

msgstr "Foolish man, when you are examined about an offense in the midst of the Order, how can you harass the Order by remaining silent?"

msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …”…"

msgstr "and after criticizing him …"

msgstr "he gave a teaching and addressed the monks, “Well then, monks, let the Order charge Channa of harassment."

msgstr "And he is to be charged in this way."

msgstr "A competent and capable monk should inform the Order:"

#. </p><span class="kamma"><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa359"></a>‘Venerables, let the Order listen to me."

msgstr "This monk Channa, when examined about an offense in the midst of the Order, harasses the Order by remaining silent."

msgstr "If it seems appropriate to the Order, the Order should charge him of harassment."

msgstr "This is the motion."

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa360"></a>Venerables, let the Order listen to me."

msgstr "This monk Channa, when examined about an offense in the midst of the Order, harasses the Order by remaining silent."

msgstr "The Order is charging him of harassment."

msgstr "Any monk who approves of charging him of harassment should remain silent."

msgstr "Any monk who does not approve should say so."

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa361"></a>The Order has charged the monk Channa of harassment."

msgstr "The Order approves and is therefore silent."

msgstr "I will remember it thus.’”"

#. </p></span><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa362"></a>After criticizing Channa in many ways for being difficult to support …"

msgstr "the Master said, “And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p class="rule">
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa363"></a>‘If a monk speaks evasively or harasses, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p>
msgstr "<a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.12.3"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.12.3.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa364"></a><strong class="term">One who speaks evasively</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "when being examined in the midst of the Order about an action that was the basis for an offense or about the class of an offense, he speaks evasively because he does not want to talk about it or reveal it, saying, “Who has committed an offense?"

msgstr "What offense has been committed? In regard to what has an offense has been committed? How has an offense been committed? Who are you talking about? What are you talking about?”—"

msgstr "this is called “one who speaks evasively.”</span>"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa365"></a><strong class="term">One who harasses</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "when being examined in the midst of the Order about an action that was the basis for an offense or about the class of an offense, he harasses the Order by remaining silent because he does not want to talk about it or reveal it—"

msgstr "this is called “one who harasses.”</span>"

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa366"></a>If he has not been charged with evasive speech, but he is being examined in the midst of the Order about an action that was the basis for an offense or about the class of an offense, and he then speaks evasively because he does not want to talk about it or reveal it, saying, “Who has committed an offense?"

msgstr "What offense has been committed? In regard to what has an offense has been committed? How has an offense been committed? Who are you talking about? What are you talking about?”"

msgstr "then he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><p>
msgstr "If he has not been charged with harassment, but he is <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.233"></a> being examined in the midst of the Order about an action that was the basis for an offense or about the class of an offense, and he then harasses the Order by remaining silent because he does not want to talk about it or reveal it, then he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><p>
msgstr "If he has been charged with evasive speech, and he is being examined in the midst of the Order about an action that was the basis for an offense or about the class of an offense, and he then speaks evasively because he does not want to talk about it or reveal it, saying, “Who has committed an offense? What offense has been committed? In regard to what has an offense has been committed? How has an offense been committed? Who are you talking about? What are you talking about?” then he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p>
msgstr "If he has been charged with harassment, and he is being examined in the midst of the Order about an action that was the basis for an offense or about the class of an offense, and he then harasses the Order by remaining silent because he does not want to talk about it or reveal it, then he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><hr><p>
msgstr "<a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.12.3.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa367"></a>If it is a legitimate procedure, and he perceives it as legitimate, and he speaks evasively and he harasses, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgstr "If it is a legitimate procedure, but he is unsure if it is, and he speaks evasively and he harasses, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgstr "If it is a legitimate procedure, but he perceives it as illegitimate, and he speaks evasively and he harasses, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p>
msgstr "If it is an illegitimate procedure, but he perceives it as legitimate, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If it is an illegitimate procedure, but he is unsure if it is, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If it is an illegitimate procedure, and he perceives it as illegitimate, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p>
msgstr "<a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.12.3.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa368"></a>There is no offense:"

msgstr "if he asks because he does not know;"

msgstr "if he does not speak because he is sick;"

msgstr "if he does not speak because he thinks there will be quarreling or disputing in the Order;"

msgstr "if he does not speak because he thinks there will be fracture or schism in the Order;"

msgstr "if he does not speak because he thinks the procedure will be illegitimate, done by <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.234"></a> an incomplete assembly, or done to one who is not subject to a procedure;"

msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta">
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa369"></a>The second rule, the training rule on evasive speech, is finished."



#. </p><hgroup><h1>
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 13: the training rule on complaining"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><h3>
msgstr "First sub-story"

#. </h3><p>
msgstr "<a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.13.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.235"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa370"></a>At one time the Buddha was staying at Rājagaha in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrel sanctuary."

msgstr "At that time Venerable Dabba the Mallian assigned the dwellings and designated the meals, and the monks Mettiya and Bhūmajaka had recently been given the full ordination.<span class="note">*<fn>"

msgstr "This rule is a follow on from Suspension 8 and 9. The comments made there on the names Mettiya and Bhūmajaka, see <ref>MS.1.1565</ref>, also apply for this rule.</fn></span>"

msgstr "They had little merit,  and they obtained inferior dwellings and meals."

msgstr "They then complained about Dabba to other monks, “Dabba the Mallian assigns dwellings and designates meals based on favoritism.”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa371"></a>The monks of few desires …"

msgstr "complained and criticized them, “How can the monks Mettiya and Bhūmajaka complain about Venerable Dabba to other monks?”…"

msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you do this?”"

msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them, “…"

msgstr "Foolish men, how can you complain about Dabba to other monks?"

msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h3>
msgstr "Preliminary ruling"

#. </h3><p class="rule">
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa372"></a>‘If a monk complains, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa373"></a>In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. </p><h3>
msgstr "Second sub-story"

#. </h3><p>
msgstr "<a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.13.2"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.236"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa374"></a>Knowing that the Master had prohibited complaining, the monks Mettiya and Bhūmajaka considered other ways of getting the monks to hear about their grievances."

msgstr "They then denounced Dabba the Mallian in the vicinity of other monks, “Dabba assigns dwellings and designates meals based on favoritism.”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

msgstr "complained and criticized them, “How can the monks Mettiya and Bhūmajaka denounce Venerable Dabba?”…"

msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you do this?”"

msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them, “…"

msgstr "Foolish men, how can you denounce Dabba?"

msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p class="rule">
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa375"></a>‘If a monk complains or denounces, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.13.3"></a>
msgstr "<a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.13.3.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa376"></a><strong class="term">Complaining</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "when someone who is fully ordained is the assigner of dwellings or the designator of meals or the distributor of rice-porridge or the distributor of fruit or the distributor of non-staple food<span class="note">*<fn><i lang="pi">Khajjaka</i>. According to <ref>Sp.4.893.16</ref> (commenting on the <i lang="pi">sekhiya</i> rules) this refers to all non-staple foods: <i lang="pi">ettha mūlakhādanīyādi sabbaṃ gahetabbaṃ</i>, “Here the non-staple foods which are roots, etc., may all be taken.”</fn></span>"

msgstr "or the distributor of small requisites, and he has been agreed upon by the Order as such, then if a monk complains about him or denounces him to one who is fully ordained—"

msgstr "desiring to disparage him, desiring to give him a bad reputation, desiring to humiliate him—"

msgstr "he commits an offense entailing confession.</span>"

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p>
msgstr "If it is a legitimate procedure, and he perceives it as legitimate, and he complains <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.237"></a> or denounces, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgstr "If it is a legitimate procedure, but he is unsure if it is, and he complains or denounces, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgstr "If it is a legitimate procedure, but he perceives it as illegitimate, and he complains or denounces, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.13.3.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa377"></a>If he complains or denounces to one who is not fully ordained, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><p>
msgstr "When someone who is fully ordained is the assigner of dwellings or the designator of meals or the distributor of rice-porridge or the distributor of fruit or the distributor of non-staple food or the distributor of small requisites, but he has not been agreed upon by the Order as such, then if a monk complains about him or denounces him to one who is fully ordained or to one who is not fully ordained—"

msgstr "desiring to disparage him, desiring to give him a bad reputation, desiring to humiliate him—"

msgstr "he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><p>
msgstr "When someone who is not fully ordained is the assigner of dwellings or the designator of meals or the distributor of rice-porridge or the distributor of fruit or the distributor of non-staple food or the distributor of small requisites, whether he has been agreed upon by the Order as such or not, then if a monk complains about him or denounces him to one who is fully ordained or to one who is not fully ordained—"

msgstr "desiring to disparage him, desiring to give him a bad reputation, desiring to humiliate him—"

msgstr "he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><p>
msgstr "If it is an illegitimate procedure, but he perceives it as legitimate, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If it is an illegitimate procedure, but he is unsure if it is, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If it is an illegitimate procedure, and he perceives it as illegitimate, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p>
msgstr "<a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.13.3.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa378"></a>There is no offense:"

msgstr "if he complains about or denounces one who normally acts from desire, ill-will, confusion, or fear;"

msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta">
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa379"></a>The third rule, the training rule on complaining, is finished."



#. </p><hgroup><h1>
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 14: the training rule on furniture"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><h3>
msgstr "First sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.14.1"></a>
msgstr "<a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.14.1.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.238"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa380"></a>At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgstr "At that time it was winter, and the monks put furniture out in the open in order to warm themselves in the sun."

msgstr "But when the time for departure was announced, they left without putting it away, getting it put away, or telling anyone."

msgstr "And the furniture was rained on."

#. </p><p>
msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

msgstr "complained and criticized them, “How can those monks put furniture out in the open and then leave without putting it away, getting it put away, or telling anyone?"

msgstr "The furniture was rained on.”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa381"></a>After criticizing those monks in many ways, they told the Master.…"

msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you did this?…"

msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p class="rule">
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa382"></a>‘If a monk takes <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.239"></a> a bed, a bench, a mattress, or a stool belonging to the Order and puts it out in the open or gets it put out, and he then leaves without putting it away, getting it put away, or telling anyone, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa383"></a>In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. </p><h3>
msgstr "Second sub-story"

#. </h3><p>
msgstr "<a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.14.1.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa384"></a>Soon afterwards monks who had stayed out in the open brought the furniture back even though it was not the rainy season."

msgstr "The Master saw this, and after giving a teaching, he addressed the monks, “<span class="rule">Monks, during the eight months outside of the rainy season, I allow you  to store furniture under a roof-cover or at the foot of a tree or wherever crows or ravens donʼt leave droppings.</span>”"

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.14.2"></a>
msgstr "<a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.14.2.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa385"></a><strong class="term">A</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "whoever …</span>"

msgstr "<strong class="term">Monk</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "…The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case.</span>"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa386"></a><strong class="term">Belonging to the Order</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "given to the Order, given up to the Order.</span>"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.240"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa387"></a><strong class="term">A bed</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "there are four kinds of beds:"

msgstr "one with legs and frame called <i lang="pi">masāraka</i>, one with legs and frame called <i lang="pi">bundikābaddha</i>, one with crooked legs, one with detachable legs.</span>"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa388"></a><strong class="term">A bench</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "there are four kinds of benches:"

msgstr "one with legs and frame called <i lang="pi">masāraka</i>, one with legs and frame called <i lang="pi">bundikābaddha</i>, one with crooked legs, one with detachable legs.</span>"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa389"></a><strong class="term">A mattress</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "there are five kinds of mattresses:"

msgstr "a mattress stuffed with wool, a mattress stuffed with cloth, a mattress stuffed with bark, a mattress stuffed with grass, a mattress stuffed with leaves.</span>"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa390"></a><strong class="term">A stool</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "one made of bark, one made of reed;<span class="note">*<fn>I have rendered khus-khus reed, <i lang="pi">muñja</i>-reed, and <i lang="pi">pabbaja</i>-reed with the single word “reed.” I am not aware that these types of reed can be properly distinguished in English.</fn></span>"

msgstr "it is upholstered and then bound together.</span>"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa391"></a><strong class="term">Puts […]"

msgstr "out</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "puts out oneself.</span>"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.241"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa392"></a><strong class="term">Gets […]"

msgstr "put out</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "gets another to put out."

msgstr "If he gets one who is not fully ordained to put it out, it is the responsibility of the monk."

msgstr "If he gets one who is fully ordained to put it out, it is the responsibility of the one who puts it out.</span>"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa393"></a><strong class="term">Leaves without putting it away</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "he does not put it away himself.</span>"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa394"></a><strong class="term">Getting it put away</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "he does not get another to put it away.</span>"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa395"></a><strong class="term">Or telling anyone</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "if he does not tell a monk, a novice monk, or a monastery worker, then when he goes beyond the distance of a stone-throw of an average man, he commits an offense entailing confession.</span>"

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p>
msgstr "<a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.14.2.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa396"></a>If it belongs to the Order, and he perceives it as belonging to the Order, and he puts it out in the open or gets it put out, and he then leaves without putting it away or getting it put away or telling anyone, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgstr "If it belongs to the Order, but he is unsure if it does …"

msgstr "If it belongs to the Order, but he perceives it as belonging to an individual, and he puts it out in the open or gets it put out, and he then leaves without putting it away or getting it put away or telling anyone, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa397"></a>If it is a mat underlay, a blanket, a <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.242"></a> floor cover, a straw mat, a leather covering, a foot-wiping cloth, or a bench made of wood, and he puts it out or gets it put out in the open, and he then leaves without putting it away or getting it put away or telling anyone, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><p>
msgstr "If it belongs to an individual, but he perceives it as belonging to the Order, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If it belongs to an individual, but he is unsure if it does, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If it belongs to an individual, and he perceives it as belonging to an individual, but that individual is not himself, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If it belongs to himself, there is no offense."

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p>
msgstr "<a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.14.2.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa398"></a>There is no offense:"

msgstr "if he leaves after putting it away;"

msgstr "if he leaves after getting it put away;"

msgstr "if he leaves after telling someone;"

msgstr "if he leaves while he is sunning it;"

msgstr "if he is obstructed;"

msgstr "if there are dangers;"

msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta">
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa399"></a>The fourth rule, the training rule on furniture, is finished."


#. </p><hgroup><h1>
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 15: the second training rule on furniture"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><p>
msgstr "<a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.15.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.243"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa400"></a>At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgstr "At that time the monks from the group of seventeen were friends."

msgstr "The lived together, and when departing they departed together."

msgstr "On one occasion they put out bedding in a dwelling belonging to the Order, but then left without putting it away, getting it put away, or telling anyone."

msgstr "And the bedding was eaten by termites."

#. </p><p>
msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

msgstr "complained and criticized them, “How can those monks from the group of seventeen put out bedding in a dwelling belonging to the Order, and then leave without putting it away, getting it put away, or telling anyone?"

msgstr "It gets eaten by termites.”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa401"></a>After criticizing those monks in many ways, they told the Master.…"

msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that those monks are acting in that way?”"

msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

msgstr "The Buddha criticized them, “…"

msgstr "How can those foolish men put out bedding in a dwelling belonging to the Order, and then leave without putting it away, getting it put away, or telling anyone, and thereby the bedding gets eaten by termites?"

msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p class="rule">
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa402"></a>‘If a monk puts out bedding in a dwelling belonging to the Order, or gets it put out, and he then leaves without putting it away, getting it put away, or telling anyone, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.15.2"></a>
msgstr "<a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.15.2.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.244"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa403"></a><strong class="term">A</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "whoever …</span>"

msgstr "<strong class="term">Monk</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "…The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is unchallengeable and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.</span>"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa404"></a><strong class="term">A dwelling belonging to the Order</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "given to the Order, given up to the Order.</span>"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa405"></a><strong class="term">Bedding</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "a mattress, a mat underlay, a blanket, a floor cover, a straw mat, a leather covering, a sitting-mat, a bed sheet, a spread of grass, a spread of leaves.</span>"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa406"></a><strong class="term">Puts out</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "puts out oneself.</span>"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa407"></a><strong class="term">Gets […] put out</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "gets another to put out.</span>"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa408"></a><strong class="term">Leaves without putting it away</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "he does not put it away himself.</span>"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa409"></a><strong class="term">Getting it put away</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "he does not get another to put it away.</span>"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa410"></a><strong class="term">Or telling anyone</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "if he does not tell a monk, a novice monk, or a  monastery worker, and he crosses the boundary of an enclosed monastery, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgstr "If he goes beyond the vicinity of an unenclosed monastery, he commits an offense entailing confession.</span>"

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p>
msgstr "<a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.15.2.2"></a>If it belongs to the Order, and he perceives it as belonging to the Order, and he puts out bedding there or gets it put out, and he then leaves without putting it away or getting it put away or telling anyone, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgstr "If it belongs to the Order, but he is unsure if it does, and he puts out bedding there or gets it put out, and he then leaves without putting it away or getting it put away or telling anyone, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgstr "If it belongs to the Order, but he perceives it as belonging to an individual, <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.245"></a> and he puts out bedding there or gets it put out, and he then leaves without putting it away or getting it put away or telling anyone, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa411"></a>If he puts out bedding, or gets it put out, in the vicinity of a dwelling, in the assembly-hall, under a roof-cover, or at the foot of a tree, and he then leaves without putting it away or getting it put away or telling anyone, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If he puts out a bed or a bench, or gets it put out, in a dwelling, in the vicinity of a dwelling, in the assembly-hall, under a roof-cover, or at the foot of a tree, and he then leaves without putting it away or getting it put away or telling anyone, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa412"></a>If it belongs to an individual, but he perceives it as belonging to the Order, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If it belongs to an individual, but he is unsure if it does, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If it belongs to an individual, and he perceives it as belonging to an individual, but that individual is not himself, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If it belongs to himself, there is no offense."

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p>
msgstr "<a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.15.2.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa413"></a>There is no offense:"

msgstr "if he leaves after putting it away;"

msgstr "if he leaves after getting it put away;"

msgstr "if he leaves after telling someone;"

msgstr "if the bedding is obstructed;"

msgstr "if he abandons his intention to return, and at that spot tells <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.246"></a> someone;"

msgstr "if he is obstructed;"

msgstr "if there are dangers;"

msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta">
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa414"></a>The fifth rule, the second training rule on furniture, is finished."

#. </p><hgroup><h1>
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 16: the training rule on encroaching"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><p>
msgstr "<a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.16.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.247"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa415"></a>At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgstr "At that time the monks from the group of six had taken possession of the best sleeping places, but the senior monks made them move."

msgstr "They thought, “What can we do so that we may dwell here during the rainy season?”"

msgstr "They then arranged their sleeping places in a way that encroached on the senior monks, thinking, “Those who feel crowded will leave.”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

msgstr "complained and criticized them, “How can the monks from the group of six arrange their sleeping places in a way that encroaches upon the senior monks?”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa416"></a>After criticizing those monks in many ways,  they told the Master.…"

msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you do this?”"

msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them, “…"

msgstr "Foolish men, how can you arrange your sleeping places in a way that encroaches on the senior monks?"

msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.248"></a> in those without it …"

msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p class="rule">
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa417"></a>‘If, in a dwelling belonging to the Order, a monk arranges his sleeping place in a way that encroaches on a monk that he knows arrived there before him, with the intention that anyone who feels crowded will leave, and he does so only for this reason and no other, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.16.2"></a>
msgstr "<a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.16.2.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa418"></a><strong class="term">A</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "whoever …</span>"

msgstr "<strong class="term">Monk</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "…The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case.</span>"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa419"></a><strong class="term">A dwelling belonging to the Order</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "given to the Order, given up to the Order.</span>"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa420"></a><strong class="term">He knows</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "he knows that he is senior, he knows that he is sick, he knows that it was given to him by the Order.</span>"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa421"></a><strong class="term">Encroaches on</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "enters after.</span>"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa422"></a><strong class="term">Arranges his sleeping place</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "if he puts out his sleeping place in the vicinity of the bed, the bench, the entry way, or the departure way, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If he sits down or lies down on it, he commits an offense entailing confession.</span>"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa423"></a><strong class="term">He does so only for this reason and no other</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "there is no other reason for arranging the sleeping place in a way that encroaches.</span>"

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p>
msgstr "<a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.16.2.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa424"></a>If it belongs to the Order, and he perceives it as belonging to the Order, and he arranges his sleeping place there in a way that encroaches, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgstr "If it belongs to the Order, but he is unsure if it does, and he arranges his sleeping place there in a way that encroaches, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgstr "If it belongs to the Order, but he perceives it as belonging to an individual, and he arranges his sleeping place there in a way that encroaches, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa425"></a>If he puts out his sleeping place, or gets it put out, anywhere apart from the vicinity of the bed, the bench, the entry way, or the departure way, <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.249"></a> he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If he sits down or lies down on it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If he puts out his sleeping place, or gets it put out, in the vicinity of a dwelling, in an assembly-hall, under a roof-cover, at the foot of a tree, or out in the open, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If he sits down or lies down on it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><p>
msgstr "If it belongs to an individual, but he perceives it as belonging to the Order, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If it belongs to an individual, but he is unsure if it does, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If it belongs to an individual, and he perceives it as belonging to an individual, but that individual is not himself, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If it belongs to himself, there is no offense."

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p>
msgstr "<a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.16.2.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa426"></a>There is no offense:"

msgstr "if he enters because he is sick;"

msgstr "if he enters because he is feeling cold or hot;"

msgstr "if there are dangers;"

msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta">
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa427"></a>The sixth rule, the training rule on encroaching, is finished."

#. </p><hgroup><h1>
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 17: the training rule on throwing out"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><p>
msgstr "<a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.17.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.250"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa428"></a>At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgstr "At that time the monks from the group of seventeen were repairing a large dwelling nearby, intending to stay there for the rainy season."

msgstr "The monks from the group of six saw this and said, “These monks from the group of seventeen are repairing a dwelling."

msgstr "Let’s throw them out.”"

msgstr "But some of them said, “Let’s wait until they’ve finished repairing it.”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa429"></a>Soon afterwards the monks from the group of six said to those from the group of seventeen, “Leave, we get this dwelling.”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "“Shouldn’t you have told us beforehand?"

msgstr "We would’ve repaired another one.”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "“Doesn’t this dwelling belong to the Order?”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "“Yes it does.”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "“Well then, leave;"

msgstr "we get this dwelling.”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "“The dwelling is large."

msgstr "You can stay here and so can we.”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.251"></a>But they said, “Leave, we get this dwelling,” and they grabbed them by the neck and threw them out in anger."

#. </p><p>
msgstr "The monks from the group of seventeen cried."

msgstr "When other monks asked them why, they told them what had happened."

#. </p><p>
msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

msgstr "complained and criticized them, “How can the monks from the group of six angrily throw other monks out of a dwelling belonging to the Order?”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa430"></a>After criticizing those monks in many ways, they told the Master.…"

msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you did this?”"

msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them, “…"

msgstr "Foolish men, how can you angrily throw other monks out of a dwelling belonging to the Order?"

msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p class="rule">
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa431"></a>‘If a monk, in anger, throws another monk out of a dwelling belonging to the Order, or gets him thrown out, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.17.2"></a>
msgstr "<a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.17.2.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa432"></a><strong class="term">A</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "whoever …</span>"

msgstr "<strong class="term">Monk</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "…The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case.</span>"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa433"></a><strong class="term">Another monk</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "a different monk.</span>"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa434"></a><strong class="term">In anger</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "discontent, having hatred, hostile.</span>"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa435"></a><strong class="term">A dwelling belonging to the Order</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "given to the Order, given up to the Order.</span>"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa436"></a><strong class="term">Throws out</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "if he takes hold of him in a room and throws him into the entrance area, he commits an <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.252"></a> offense entailing confession."

msgstr "If he takes hold of him in the entrance area and throws him outside, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgstr "Even if he makes him go through many doors with a single effort, he commits one offense entailing confession.</span>"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa437"></a><strong class="term">Gets […] thrown out</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "if he asks another, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgstr "If he only asks once, then even if the other makes him go through many doors, he commits one offense entailing confession.</span>"

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p>
msgstr "<a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.17.2.2"></a>"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa438"></a>If it belongs to the Order, and he perceives it as belonging to the Order, and in anger he throws him out or gets him thrown out, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgstr "If it belongs to the Order, but he is unsure if it does, and in anger he throws him out or gets him thrown out, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgstr "If it belongs to the Order, but he perceives it as belonging to an individual, and in anger he throws him out or gets him thrown out, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa439"></a>If he throws out one of his requisites, or he gets it thrown out, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If he throws him out or gets him thrown out from the vicinity of a dwelling, from an assembly-hall, from under a roof-cover, from the foot of a tree, or from a space out in the open, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If he throws out one of his requisites from any of these places, or he gets it thrown out, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If he throws out one who is not fully ordained, or gets them thrown out, from a dwelling, from the vicinity of a dwelling, from an assembly-hall, from under a roof-cover, from the foot of a tree, or from a space out in the open, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If he throws out one of his requisites from any of these places, or gets it thrown out, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa440"></a>If it belongs to an individual, but he perceives it as belonging to the Order, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If it belongs to an individual, but he is unsure if it does, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If it belongs to an individual, and he perceives it as belonging to an individual, but that individual is not himself, he commits an offense of wrong <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.253"></a> conduct."

msgstr "If it belongs to himself, there is no offense."

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p>
msgstr "<a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.17.2.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa441"></a>There is no offense:"

msgstr "if he throws out, or gets thrown out, one who is shameless;"

msgstr "if he throws out, or gets thrown out, a requisite belonging to that person;"

msgstr "if he throws out, or gets thrown out, one who is insane;"

msgstr "if he throws out, or gets thrown out, a requisite belonging to that person;"

msgstr "if he throws out, or gets thrown out, one who is quarrelsome and disputatious, who creates legal issues in the Order;"

msgstr "if he throws out, or gets thrown out, a requisite belonging to that person;"

msgstr "if he throws out, or gets thrown out, a pupil or student who is not acting appropriately;"

msgstr "if he throws out, or gets thrown out, a requisite belonging to that person;"

msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta">
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa442"></a>The seventh rule, the training rule on throwing out, is finished."


#. </p><hgroup><h1>
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 18: the training rule on upper stories"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><p>
msgstr "<a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.18.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.254"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa443"></a>At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgstr "At that  time two monks were staying in a dwelling with an upper story belonging to the Order, one staying below and one above."

msgstr "The monk above sat down suddenly on a bed with detachable legs."

msgstr "A leg fell off and hit the monk below on the head."

msgstr "He cried out."

msgstr "Monks came rushing to and asked him why, and he told them what had happened."

#. </p><p>
msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

msgstr "complained and criticized him, “How can a monk sit down suddenly on a bed with detachable legs on an upper story in a dwelling belonging to the Order?”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa444"></a>After criticizing that monk in many ways, they told the Master.…"

msgstr "“Is it true, monk, that you did this?”"

msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

msgstr "The Buddha rebuked him, “…"

msgstr "Foolish man, how can you sit down suddenly on a bed with detachable legs on a upper story in a dwelling belonging to the Order?"

msgstr "<a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.255"></a> This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p class="rule">
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa445"></a>‘If a monk sits down or lies down on a bed or a bench with detachable legs on an upper story<span class="note">*<fn>I am here taking <i lang="pi">kuṭi</i> to refer to the upper story itself, rather than the whole building, which already has the separate name <i lang="pi">vihāra</i>.</fn></span>"

msgstr "in a dwelling belonging to the Order, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.18.2"></a>
msgstr "<a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.18.2.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa446"></a><strong class="term">A</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "whoever …</span>"

msgstr "<strong class="term">Monk</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "…The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case.</span>"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa447"></a><strong class="term">A dwelling belonging to the Order</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "given to the Order, given up to the Order.</span>"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa448"></a><strong class="term">An upper story</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "a man of average height does not hit his head.</span>"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa449"></a><strong class="term">A bed with detachable legs</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "inserting the limbs, it stands.</span>"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa450"></a><strong class="term">A bench with detachable legs</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "inserting the limbs, it stands.</span>"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa451"></a><strong class="term">Sits down</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "if he sits down on it, he commits an offense entailing confession.</span>"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa452"></a><strong class="term">Lies down</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "if he lies down on it, he commits an offense entailing confession.</span>"

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p>
msgstr "<a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.18.2.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa453"></a>If it belongs to the Order, and he perceives it as belonging to the Order, and he sits down or lies down on a bed or a bench with detachable legs on the upper story, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgstr "If it belongs to the Order, but he is unsure if it does …"

msgstr "If it belongs to the Order, but he perceives it as belonging to an individual, <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.256"></a> and he sits down or lies down on a bed or a bench with detachable legs on the upper story, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa454"></a>If it belongs to an individual, but he perceives it as belonging to the Order, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If it belongs to an individual, but he is unsure if it does, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If it belongs to an individual, and he perceives it as belonging to an individual, but that individual is not himself, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If it belongs to himself, there is no offense."

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p>
msgstr "<a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.18.2.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa455"></a>There is no offense:"

msgstr "if there is no upper story;"

msgstr "if the upper story is so low that one hits the head;"

msgstr "if the lower story is not in use;"

msgstr "if the upper story has floorboards;"

msgstr "if bolts to fasten the legs have been applied<span class="note">*<fn><i lang="pi">Dinnā</i>.</fn></span>,"

msgstr "if he stands on it to get hold of something or to put something up;"

msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta">
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa456"></a>The eighth rule, the training rule on upper stories, is finished."

HIER
#. </p><hgroup><h1>
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 19: the training rule on large dwellings"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><p>
msgstr "<a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.19.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.257"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa457"></a>At one time the Buddha was staying at Kosambī in Ghosita’s Monastery."

msgstr "At that time a minister who was Venerable Channa’s supporter was making him a dwelling."

msgstr "When the dwelling was finished, Channa had it roofed and plastered again and again."

msgstr "Being overloaded, the dwelling collapsed."

msgstr "Then, while collecting grass and sticks, Channa spoiled the barley field belonging to a certain brahmin."

msgstr "That brahmin grumbled and complained, “How can the Venerables spoil my barley field?”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa458"></a>The monks heard the complaints of that brahmin, and the monks of few desires …"

msgstr "complained and criticized Channa, “How can Venerable Channa get a finished dwelling roofed and plastered again and again, so that it collapsed from overloading?”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa459"></a>After criticizing him in many ways, they told the Master.…"

msgstr "“Is it true, Channa, that you did this?”"

msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

msgstr "The Buddha rebuked him, “…"

msgstr "Foolish man, how can you get a finished dwelling roofed and plastered again and again, so that it collapses from overloading?"

msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p class="rule">
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa460"></a>‘When a monk is building a large dwelling, <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.258"></a> then standing where there are no cultivated plants, he may apply two or three courses of covering,<span class="note">*<fn><i lang="pi">Dvatticchadanassa pariyāyaṃ […] adhiṭṭhātabbaṃ,</i> “a succession of two or three coverings may be applied.”</fn></span> taking it as far as the door frame and using it for fixing the door bolt and for treating the window shutters."

msgstr "If he applies more than that, even if he stands where there are no cultivated plants, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.19.2"></a>
msgstr "<a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.19.2.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa461"></a><strong class="term">A large dwelling</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "one with an owner is what is meant.</span>"

msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa462"></a><strong class="term">A dwelling</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "plastered inside or plastered outside or plastered both inside and outside.</span>"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa463"></a><strong class="term">Building</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "building or getting built.</span>"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa464"></a><strong class="term">As far as the door frame</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "a distance of an arm’s reach next to the lintel and the door-posts.</span>"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa465"></a><strong class="term">For fixing the door bolt</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "for the fixing of the door.</span>"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa466"></a><strong class="term">For treating the window shutters</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "for treating <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.259"></a> the windows there is white color, black color, treating with red ocher, making a garland pattern, making a creeper pattern, a pattern of sword-fish teeth,<span class="note">*<fn><i lang="pi">Makaradantaka</i>. Lit. “Like the teeth of a <i lang="pi">makara</i>.” In later Buddhism the <i lang="pi">makara</i> is the name of a mythological marine animal, but what it refers to in this context is not clear. According to Sp-yoj.3.243 <i lang="pi">makara</i> is the name of a certain species of fish:" <i lang="pi">Makaradantaketi makaranāmakassa macchassa dantasadise dante</i>. “Swordfish” is merely a tentative rendering taken from PED.</fn></span>"

msgstr "the five-cloth pattern.<span class="note"><i lang="pi">Pañcapaṭika</i>. Vmv.4.299(VRI): <i lang="pi">Pāḷiyaṃ pañcapaṭikanti jātiādipañcappakāravaṇṇamaṭṭhaṃ</i>, “<i lang="pi">Pañcapaṭika</i> in the canonical text means the five-fold appearance, starting with jasmine.” The meaning is not clear, especially of <i lang="pi">jāti</i>.</fn></span></span>"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa467"></a><strong class="term">Standing where there are no cultivated plants, he may apply two or three courses of covering</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "if he applies it while standing where there are cultivated plants, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "For someone covering in lines,<span class="note">*<fn><i lang="pi">Maggena</i>, explained by the commentary (<ref>Sp.4.785.12</ref>) as, “not encircling, just straight covering,” <i lang="pi">aparikkhipitvā ujukameva chādanaṃ</i>.</fn></span>"

msgstr "after covering with two layers,<span class="note">*<fn><i lang="pi">Dve magge</i>, “two lines.” The context requires that this must refer to lines on top of each other rather than next to each other.</fn></span>"

msgstr "he may ask for a third layer, and he should then depart.<span class="note">*<fn><i lang="pi">Pakkamitabbaṃ</i>. The point, according to <ref>Sp.4.785.21</ref>, seems to be that he may not keep on asking: “If he does not depart, he should stand in silence,” <i lang="pi">sace na pakkamati, tuṇhībhūtena ṭhātabbaṃ</i>.</fn></span>"

msgstr "For someone covering in circles, after covering with two layers, he may ask for a third layer, and he should then depart.</span>"

msgstr "<strong class="term">Cultivated plants</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "vegetables and grains.</span><span class="note">I have moved this last definition from the beginning of the paragraph to the end to make the translation clearer.</fn></span>"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa468"></a><strong class="term">If he applies more than that, even if he stands where there are no cultivated plants</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "if he is covering with bricks, then for every brick, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgstr "If he is covering with rocks, then for every rock, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgstr "If he is covering with plaster, then for every lump, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgstr "If he is covering with grass, then for every handful, he commits an <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.260"></a> offense entailing confession."

msgstr "If he is covering with leaves, then for every leaf, he commits an offense entailing confession.</span>"

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p>
msgstr "<a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.19.2.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa469"></a>If it is more than two or three courses, and he perceives it as more, and he applies it, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgstr "If it is more than two or three courses, but he is unsure if it is, and he applies it, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgstr "If it is more than two or three courses, but he perceives it as less, and he applies it, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa469"></a>If it is less than two or three courses, but he perceives it as more, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If it is less than two or three courses, but he is unsure if it is, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If it is less than two or three courses, and he perceives it as less, there is no offense."

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p>
msgstr "<a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.19.2.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa471"></a>There is no offense:"

msgstr "if he applies two or three courses;"

msgstr "if he applies less than two or three courses;"

msgstr "if it is a shelter;"

msgstr "if it is a cave;"

msgstr "if it is a grass hut;"

msgstr "if it is for the benefit of someone else;"

msgstr "if it is by means of his own property;"

msgstr "if it is anything other than a place to dwell in;"

msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta">
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa472"></a>The ninth rule, the training rule on large dwellings, is finished."

#. </p><hgroup><h1>
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 20: the training rule on containing living beings"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><p>
msgstr "<a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.20.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.261"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa473"></a>At one time the Buddha was staying at Āḷavī at the Aggāḷava Shrine."

msgstr "At that time the monks at Āḷavī were doing building work."

msgstr "And they poured water that they knew contained living beings onto grass and clay, and they got others to do the same."

msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

msgstr "complained and criticized them, “How can the monks at Āḷavī pour water that they know contains living beings onto grass and clay, and get others to do the same?”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "After criticizing those monks in many ways, they told the Master.…"

msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you do this?”"

msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them, “…"

msgstr "Foolish men, how can you pour water that you know contains living beings onto grass and clay, and get others to do the same?"

msgstr " This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p class="rule">
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa474"></a>‘If a monk pours, or gets poured, water that he knows contains living beings onto grass or clay, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.20.2"></a>
msgstr "<a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.20.2.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa475"></a><strong class="term">A</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "whoever …</span>"

msgstr "<strong class="term">Monk</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "…The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case.</span>"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa476"></a><strong class="term">He knows</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "he knows by himself or others have told him.</span>"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa477"></a><strong class="term">Pours</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "he pours it himself.</span>"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa478"></a><strong class="term">Gets poured</strong>:"

#. <span class="gloss">
msgstr "if he asks another, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgstr "If he only asks once, then even if the other pours many times, he commits one offense entailing confession.</span>"

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p>
msgstr "<a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.20.2.2"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.262"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa479"></a>If it contains living beings, and he perceives it as containing living beings, and he pours it onto grass or clay, or he gets it poured, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgstr "If it contains living beings, but he is unsure if it does, and he pours it onto grass or clay, or he gets it poured, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If it contains living beings, but he perceives it as not containing living beings, and he pours it onto grass or clay, or he gets it poured, there is no offense."

#. </p><p>
msgstr "If it does not contain living beings, but he perceives it as containing living beings, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If it does not contain living beings, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If it does not contain living beings, and he perceives it as not containing living beings, there is no offense."

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p>
msgstr "<a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.20.2.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa480"></a>There is no offense:"

msgstr "if it is unintentional;"

msgstr "if he is not mindful;"

msgstr "if he does not know;"

msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta">
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa481"></a>The tenth rule, the training rule on containing living beings, is finished."

#. </p><p class="endchapter">
msgstr "The second chapter on plants is finished."

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa482"></a>This is the summary:"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "<uddana><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa483"></a>Being, with another,"

#. <br>
msgstr "Complaining, the two with departing;"

#. <br>
msgstr "Before, throwing out, removable,"

#. <br>
msgstr "Door, and containing living beings.</uddana>"

